The second featured brew of our Foragerfest barrel aged bottle release is Derby Pie! 

“Hard to not love Derby Pie!  I enjoyed derby pie (the actual dessert) @harborviewpepin in Pepin, WI last summer and after one bite I knew we had to create a beer inspired by this nutty, chocolatey, creamy delight. Not to mention Kyle from Horus Aged Ales is one the kindness brewers in the industry—you could say he’s as sweet as pie 😉. “ Annie Henderson, Forager Brewery owner. 

The full September 18th Foragerfest details can be found  is the link in our profile.

First beer with Uncle Dino and the rest of the @vitaminseabrewing crew drops in Weymouth tomorrow!
.
Repost @vitaminseabrewing with @get.repost
・・・
SATURDAY 8/21/21 
OPEN FOR ONSITE POURS AND CANS TO GO

Oh When Right DIPA (8%) hopped with  HBC 522, Pacific Sunrise, Sultana, and Zamba. over the last few years we’ve formed a friendship with Kyle from @horusagedales - in addition to beer we’ve always talked surfing and our mutual love of the ocean. When we decided to collab we figured the names would be a take on our favorite surfer’s names.  The first of these collabs is named after Owen Wright. His story is one of inspiration. In 2015, @owright was  fifth in the World Surfing League and was looking forward to finishing his best season. While he was training for his final competition he had a bad wipeout and suffered blood effusion in his brain. As a result of this wipeout he had to learn how to walk again among other basic functions. Through hard work and perseverance he not only learned how to walk but also surf again.  At the age of 31, in the Tokyo Olympics, Owen won a bronze medal for Australia.  Truly an inspiring story. 🙏🏼🙏🏼

OPENING CASE COUNTS

node.text:
Lupomax x Lupomax x Lupomax x Lupomax with @eqbrewery 🐸!
.
Repost @eqbrewery with @get.repost
・・・
Today at Noon, we will sell Hyla Versicolor, our latest collaboration with @horusagedales (8.5 % DIPA) $20 per 4-pk, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Pennsylvania, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Kentucky, Vermont, Nebraska, North Dakota, and Virginia. Please follow State Limitations if you’re placing out of State delivery.

Latin for "variable color", this North East treefrog and its versicolor abilities can hit all the colorful flavors found in this New England DIPA. To super saturate the spectrum on your palate, this beer is brewed entirely with Lupomax Citra, Lupomax Mosaic, Lupomax Idaho 7, and Lupomax Sabro. Pouring a deep hazy yellow with aromatic pops of pineapple, cannabis, citrus, and crushed berry you’ll notice intense flavors of juicy citrus, ripe rainbow melon, berry medley, and a touch of pine blend into an #EQjuice finish.

Illustration by @juliagreenartistwhosings
